caption:
Hot girls and boys upcycle ğŸŒ â™»ï¸ Here are some clever tips on how to reuse your empties from our friend @alyssamjulian â˜€ï¸

1. Be sure to clean thoroughly before repurposing â™»ï¸

2. Reuse any lidded jar for kitchen storage (like spices!) or for storing salts on the go. 

3. Repurpose empty spray bottles into DIY room sprays! Use 1.5 oz of distilled water, 1.5 oz vodka, essential oils of your choice. Add to bottle, give it a shake, and spritz freely! 

4. Use any size bottle to grow new plant pals ğŸŒ± Simply cut on an angle and add to filtered water, then watch them grow! 

5. Create your own DIY infused olive oil. Chop 1 clove of garlic (could also use herbs!) and add to bottle with oil. Close the lid and let it do its thing!

What are some of your favorite ways to upcycle your empties? Let us know below! ğŸ‘‡ #oseamalibu

caption:
As a brand inspired by the ocean, we have a distinct duty to protect our deepest source. Caring for our planet has been a core part of our ethos since 1996. But in 2021 we took our commitment to the next level by becoming Climate Neutral. We are now a Climate Neutral Certified brand with @beclimateneutral because sustainability efforts are no longer optional ğŸŒ 

So how did we get here? ğŸ¤”

1. We measured our carbon footprint
2. Offset it via carbon credits
3. Created a plan to reduce our future carbon emissions

What we did to reduce our 2021 emissions:
âœ”ï¸Transitioned all of our product cartons to 100% FSC certified paper.
âœ”ï¸ Reduced excess waste by removing paper inserts from our product unit boxes.
âœ”ï¸ Increased the percentage of eco-friendly materials for all our productâ€™s packaging.
âœ”ï¸ Reduced our consumption by switching our office + skincare studio to 100% green energy sources.

What we are doing to reduce our 2022 emissions:
âœ”ï¸Transition our pumps and lids to post-consumer materials.
âœ”ï¸Increase the percentage of PCR paper used.
âœ”ï¸Reduce excess waste in each customer shipment through improved sizing logic & removing printed materials.

Learn more via our link in bio! #oseamalibu

caption:
Need inspiration for a healthy weeknight dinner? âœ¨ Look no further than this recipe by our friend @commonplacecook!

Black Kale and Pomegranate Salad with Creamy Tahini Dressing (1 Serving) ğŸ¥— 

Salad Dressing: 
1 Tbsp Olive Oil
2 Tbsp Tahini 
1 tsp Maple Syrup 
1 tsp Lemon Juice 
1 Clove of Garlic, minced 
Pinch of flaky salt and black pepper
1-2 teaspoons of cold water

Salad Base:
2 cups of black kale
Half a cup of mini cucumbers, sliced 
Half an avocado, diced 
Tablespoon of fresh dill, chopped 
Handful of pomegranate seeds
Two tablespoons of chopped almonds 

Instructions: 
1. Mix together all salad dressing ingredients until well incorporated. If the consistency is too thick, add one teaspoon of cold water in at a time until preferred consistency is achieved. Set aside. 

2. Chop up black kale into thin ribbons. Drizzle with olive oil and salt. Massage kale to break down any toughness or bitterness. 

3. Add cucumbers, avocado and dill. Toss salad with Tahini dressing

4. Top with pomegranate seeds, chopped almonds, and any remaining cucumbers. 

Enjoy! ğŸ¥° #oseamalibu
